1. Opertaing System Upgrade:

Master Node, Worker Node-1, Worker Node-2, Worker Node-3

When we plan to upgrade or do any patches on the Worker Node-01. It goes down for a while.
Pod on node-01 will be placed on other node-2, node-3 if it has replica set.

Also if node goes down for mote than 5 minutes. Worker node will decide the node is dead. New pods will be created in the other nodes.
Once node-01 comes back, the pod will be placed in node-01


There is an another way to implement the upgrade or patches without impacting the pods.


# kubectl drain node-1 
We can apply drain on the node-1, if node-01 goes down, the pods in the node-1 will be moved to other nodes.
We can't schedule the pods on the node-1 until if goes down and back to it. Then applying the uncodon on it. We can schedule the pods.
This only works when replica set is applied to the pods.

# kubectl uncordon node-1
We need to apply uncordon on the node-1, saying the scheduler to schedule the pods on the node-01 once uncordon on the node-01

Note:
The pods which is moved to other nodes will not be back to node01 until the existing pods deleted or new pods created on the node2, node3

# kubectl cordon node2
We can't schedule a new pods on the node2



